## Review Result: FAILED

### Summary

The token migration for issue #69 is **incomplete**. While the implementation made good progress on replacing hex/rgb values in JS objects with `var(--color-*)` references and added solid theme infrastructure (glass utilities, shadow tokens, brand colors, keyframe consolidation), it left **~219 Tailwind default palette classes** unchanged across all 10 consumer apps.

### Critical Gap

Classes like `text-amber-400`, `bg-green-500/15`, `border-pink-400`, `text-emerald-400` etc. still use Tailwind's built-in palette instead of the project's custom theme tokens (`accent`, `green`, `red`, `pill-*`, etc.). This violates the acceptance criterion **"All colors reference theme tokens."**

**Violations by app:**
| App | Remaining |
|-----|-----------|
| soccer-training | 39 |
| hspt-tutor | 35 |
| roblox-dances | 33 |
| hspt-practice | 25 |
| cringe-rizzler | 24 |
| dad-joke-of-the-day | 20 |
| slang-translator | 17 |
| proper-wine-pour | 15 |
| age-of-apes | 7 |
| generations | 4 |

### What was done well
- Theme token infrastructure in `theme.css` and `globals.css` is solid
- Hex values in JS config objects replaced with `var()` references
- Glass utility classes consolidated
- Keyframe animations moved from inline `<style>` to globals
- `color-mix()` usage correctly references CSS variables

### What needs to happen next
Each remaining Tailwind default palette class needs to be mapped to the project's theme tokens. For example:
- `amber-400/500` -> `accent`
- `green-400/500` -> `green`
- `pink-400/500` -> `pill-6`
- `emerald-400` -> `green`
- `purple-400/500` -> `pill-0`
- `blue-400` -> `blue`
- `red-400/500` -> `red`

### Additional notes
- `themeColor` hex values in metadata are **acceptable** (browser API requirement)
- Canvas colors in cringe-rizzler are **acceptable** (Canvas API requirement)
- The branch also modifies ~30 internal/command-center apps which belong to issue #68, adding scope noise